RDNA4 fix: enable triton attention for NemotronH Mamba2-hybrid models.

Applies AFTER patch 001 (upstream-sync), which already carries the SWA-aware
triton attention path (swa_attn_logits, HybridLinearKVPool layers_mapping +
translate_loc_from_full_to_swa in forward_extend/decode). This patch adds the
one remaining piece for Mamba2-Transformer hybrids: TritonAttnBackend.__init__
samples the value head dim via get_value_buffer(0), but in such a hybrid the
full-attention layers live at sparse indices (NemotronH-Nano-Omni:
[5,12,19,26,33,42]) and layer 0 is a Mamba layer with no entry in the
HybridLinearKVPool's full_attention_layer_id_mapping -> "ValueError: layer_id=0
not in full attention layers" -> triton attention can't init, so the model is
stuck on torch_native (whose only ROCm SDPA backend is MATH -> materializes
O(chunk x context) scores -> OOM past ~150K). The backend already special-cases
hybrid_gdn / kimi_linear / linear_attn_model_spec, but those miss the Nano-Omni
config class (loaded via trust-remote-code; mamba2_config doesn't recognize it).
Fix: also duck-type on the pool -- any HybridLinearKVPool exposes
get_v_head_dim() (samples the full_kv_pool's first full-attention layer), so use
it whenever present.

Unblocks triton flash attention (memory-efficient, full 256K) for NemotronH
hybrids: Nemotron-Omni serves a 247K-tok prefill at full-token-usage 0.07 (no
OOM), ~109s, ~29 tok/s. (gemma-4 SWA models reach triton via 001's SWA path +
the triton preset default -- they take the sliding_window branch, not this
hybrid branch -- e.g. gemma-4-26B: 110K-tok prefill, no OOM, ~16.5 tok/s.)
Pure-additive condition; CUDA + non-hybrid pools (MHATokenToKVPool, no
get_v_head_dim) unaffected. Applies after 001.

